<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Upper Mount Royal </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Upper Mount Royal has always been the home to Calgaryâ€™s elite. Dating back to more than a
                century, some of the houses here are over 100 years old! </p>
            <p class="par-xl">The houses are built in the typical classic red-brick style and make for a very
                picturesque location what with the scenic surroundings of Upper Mount Royal. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The community has preserved its exclusivity as one of the most prime locations to have a
                home, and it remains one such to this day.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">The average price of a house in 2016 was $1,712,000. Almost all the houses are detached,
                single-family properties, as can be expected in a neighborhood such as Upper Mount Royal. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">When considering the purchase of property in Upper Mount Royal, be careful of getting
                confused with Lower Royal Mount, which is not as high-class as Upper Mount Royal. Naturally, the options
                on Upper Mount Royal are fewer, more expensive, but located at the choicest most convenient spots.</p>

        </div>
